Commentary Text: Chakaravarthy to Shahbaz Ahmed, out Stumped!! Was that needed? The batter danced down, was beaten in flight and the ball turned away for the keeper to whip the bails off. The batter danced down blind and that didn't help as the bowler slowed it down and got it to turn away as well. The keeper didn't falter and did the needful. Shahbaz Ahmed has done his job but would be a little disappointed as he was hitting them so well on a track where most batters have struggled. Shahbaz Ahmed st Jackson b Chakaravarthy 27(20) [6s-3]

Commentary Text: Umesh Yadav to Anuj Rawat, out Caught by Jackson!! A wicket in the first over for KKR as Umesh strikes! Lovely delivery. Short of length in the channel, climbs on Rawat as he tries steering it to third. The edge is found very high on the bat, flies to the left of Jackson who grabs it comfortably. Anuj Rawat c Jackson b Umesh Yadav 0(2)
